         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24 March 1889. ¶  ¶ To my great joy, dear Mr Holtze, your letter of 9 March ¶  and your small packet of plants arrived today. In the next few days I shall compare both the  ¶ Pogonia ¶  species No. 86...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">89.03.24a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">24/3/89</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zu meiner grossen Freude, geehrter Herr Holtze, kam heute Ihr Schreiben vom 9 März u Ihr Päckchen Pflanzen an. In den nächsten Tagen werde ich die beiden <name key="Pogonia">Pogonia</name> Arten 860 &amp; 861 mit denen von Queensland u anderen Ländern vergleichen, auch die <name key="Eulophia">Eulophia</name> 862</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Könnten Sie von der kleinen Schlingpflanze 791 wohl </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Frucht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> senden, einfach in einem Couvert. Ohne solche lässt sich das Genus nicht bestimmen, denn es sind bereits 7000 Arten aus der Familie der <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> beschrieben. Sie können also denken, wie schwierig es ist, sich unter soviel Pflanzen dieser Ordnung zurecht zu finden, zumal da manche tropische Formen sich über die westl. sowohl als die östl.</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M omitted a word here, probably 'Halbkugel'.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style=""> </seg>erstrecken</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">Die Centennial Ausstellung ist nun vorüber; so werde ich wohl etwas mehr Ruhe bekommen zum Beschreiben von Pflanzen in 1889. Ich habe manche Ihrer Sendungen zur Ausstellung bewundert. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hoffentlich haben Sie die 7te Ausgabe der "Select plants" erhalten durch die Public Library von Melbourne.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihrem Wunsche gemäss sende ich wieder Wurzelausläufer von <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie ehrend und Ihnen alles Gute wünschend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 March 1889.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>To my great joy, dear Mr Holtze, your letter of 9 March<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> and your small packet of plants arrived today. In the next few days I shall compare both the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Pogonia">Pogonia</name>
               </seg> species No. 860 and 861<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The result of the comparison is in M to M. Holtze, 7 April 1889.</p>
               </note> with those from Queensland and other countries, also the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eulophia">Eulophia</name>
               </seg> No. 862.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In M to M. Holtze, 20 October 1888, M requested further details of 'the slender orchid', which was apparently mislaid when he went to work on it (see M to M. Holtze, 26 January 1889 (<seg style="">in this edition as 89-01-26a))</seg>. M to M. Holtze, 12 June 1889, contains M's identification.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be possible to send <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruit</hi>
               </seg> of the little climbing plant No. 791,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to M. Holtze, 1889.</p>
               </note> just in an envelope. Without them it is not possible to determine the genus, as already 7000 species have been described in the family <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name>. So you can imagine how difficult it is to find one's way around so many plants of this order, especially as many tropical forms extend across the western as well as the eastern [...].<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M omitted a word here in his text, probably intending 'hemisphere'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Centennial Exhibition is now over, so I may get a little more peace in 1889 to describe plants. I have admired many of your entries to the Exhibition.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Centennial International Exhibition, Melbourne (1888), pp. 99-101. In the Northern Territory of South Australia section, Holtze had six exhibits: No 7, Babool tree; no 17, jute, flax, cotton, hemp &amp;c; no 20, arrowroot tapioca, mandioca, sweet potato, and yam starch; no 22, nutritious and condiment tubers; no 24, sugar cane; no. 70 agricultural soil. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you have received the 7th edition of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Select plants</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.12.01.</p>
               </note> through the Public Library of Melbourne.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">The Public Library distributed all Victorian Government Printing Office publications at this period.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>According to your wish I am sending you once more rooted runners of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to M. Holtze, 4 May 1888 (in this edition as 88-05-04b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sending you my respects and wishing you all the best</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eulophia">Eulophia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pogonia">Pogonia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
